/**
 * @file SystemCore.dox
 * @brief Overview of examples for the MIDILAR SystemCore module.
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_Examples_SystemCore SystemCore Examples
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_Examples
 * @brief Examples demonstrating timing and callback infrastructure in `SystemCore`.
 *
 * ---
 *
 * The `SystemCore` module provides low-level infrastructure tools such as platform-independent
 * callback routing and real-time timekeeping utilities.
 *
 * This example group covers usage of the two foundational classes:
 *
 * - `CallbackHandler<TArgs..., TResult>`: A lightweight mechanism for binding and invoking callbacks.
 * - `Clock`: A polling-compatible system timer abstraction designed to interface with hardware time sources.
 *
 * ---
 *
 * ## Example Categories
 *
 * - @ref MIDILAR_Examples_SystemCore_CallbackHandler
 * - @ref MIDILAR_Examples_SystemCore_Clock
 *
 * ---
 *
 * ## Standard C++ Version
 * These examples run under desktop environments using simulated timers and console-based output.
 *
 * ### How to Run
 * Build the example via CMake and run the corresponding executable:
 *
 * ```sh
 * cmake -B build
 * cmake --build build
 * ./build/bin/CallbackHandler_Usage
 * ```
 *
 * ---
 *
 * ## Arduino-Compatible Version
 * The Arduino versions are simplified to compile in embedded environments.
 *
 * ### How to Run
 * Open from the Arduino IDE using:
 *
 * ```text
 * File → Examples → MIDILAR → SystemCore → CallbackHandler
 * ```
 *
 * Upload to your board and use **Serial Monitor** at 115200 baud to view runtime behavior.
 *
 * ---
 *
 * ## See Also
 * - @ref MIDILAR::SystemCore::Clock
 * - @ref MIDILAR::SystemCore::CallbackHandler
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_Examples_CallbackHandler CallbackHandler Examples
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_Examples_SystemCore
 * @brief Examples for binding, unbinding, and invoking generic callbacks.
 */

/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_Examples_Clock Clock Class Examples
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_Examples_SystemCore
 * @brief Examples for reading and updating timing data using the `Clock` class.
 */
